.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Digest::Result \- Result of digesting a transaction
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        my $digest = $tx\->get_digest(...);
\&
\&        say to_format [hex => $digest];
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a simple class that holds the result of digesting a transaction by
"get_digest" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction and similar methods. It stringifies
automatically to "preimage", or throws an exception if there is no preimage.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fItaproot\fR
.IX Subsection "taproot"
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor\fR.
.PP
This boolean flag controls whether legacy (when false, uses \f(CW\*(C`hash256\*(C'\fR) or
taproot (when true, uses \f(CW\*(C`tagged_hash\*(C'\fR) hashing should be used to obtain
"hash" from "preimage". Default: \f(CW\*(C`false\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\fIpreimage\fR
.IX Subsection "preimage"
.PP
\&\fIAvailable in the constructor\fR.
.PP
This bytestring is a preimage of the transaction. Note that preimage can not be
set in some edge cases.
.PP
\&\fIpredicate:\fR \f(CW\*(C`has_preimage\*(C'\fR
.PP
